          <div class="content-section">
            <div class="section-header"><span class="section-tag">Overview</span><h2>Fixed Deposit Interest Rates in India</h2></div>
            <p>Fixed Deposits (FDs) remain India's most popular savings instrument, offering guaranteed returns, capital protection, and flexible tenures. With over ₹200 lakh crore in outstanding bank deposits, FDs form the backbone of household savings in India. The interest rate you earn depends on the bank, tenure, deposit amount, and whether you're a senior citizen.</p>
            <p>In 2026, FD rates across major banks range from 6.50% to 7.30% for general customers, while NBFCs like Bajaj Finance offer up to 8.05%. Senior citizens enjoy an additional 0.25%–0.50% premium. Rates vary significantly by tenure, with the sweet spot typically being 1–3 year deposits where banks offer their highest rates.</p>
            <p>Bank FDs up to ₹5 lakh are insured by the Deposit Insurance and Credit Guarantee Corporation (DICGC), providing an extra layer of safety. For larger deposits, choosing top-rated banks and diversifying across institutions is recommended.</p>
          </div>

