          <div class="content-section">
            <div class="section-header"><span class="section-tag">Benefits</span><h2>Why Choose Fixed Deposits?</h2></div>
            <ul class="feature-list">
              <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i><div><strong>Guaranteed Returns</strong><p>FD interest rates are fixed at the time of deposit and remain unchanged throughout the tenure. Your returns are predictable from day one, unaffected by market fluctuations or economic conditions.</p></div></li>
              <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i><div><strong>Capital Protection with DICGC Insurance</strong><p>Bank FDs up to ₹5 lakh per depositor per bank are insured by DICGC. Your principal is completely safe, making FDs one of the most secure investment options available in India.</p></div></li>
              <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i><div><strong>Flexible Tenure Options</strong><p>Choose tenures from 7 days to 10 years based on your financial goals. Short-term FDs are great for parking surplus funds, while longer tenures typically offer higher interest rates.</p></div></li>
              <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i><div><strong>Tax Saving FD Under Section 80C</strong><p>5-year tax-saving FDs qualify for deduction up to ₹1.5 lakh under Section 80C of the Income Tax Act. This is a risk-free tax-saving option for conservative investors.</p></div></li>
              <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i><div><strong>Loan Against FD Facility</strong><p>You can borrow up to 90% of your FD value at interest rates just 1%–2% above the FD rate. This provides instant liquidity without breaking your deposit and losing interest.</p></div></li>
              <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i><div><strong>Senior Citizen Premium Rates</strong><p>Senior citizens (60+) receive an additional 0.25%–0.50% interest on FDs across all banks. Some banks offer even higher premiums for super senior citizens (80+), making FDs especially attractive for retirees.</p></div></li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="content-section">
            <div class="section-header"><span class="section-tag">How to Invest</span><h2>How to Open a Fixed Deposit</h2></div>
            <div class="steps-grid">
              <div class="step-card"><div class="step-num">1</div><h3>Compare Rates</h3><p>Use our rate comparison table to identify the bank or NBFC offering the best rate for your preferred tenure. Consider NBFC FDs for higher returns if you're comfortable with the slightly different risk profile.</p></div>
              <div class="step-card"><div class="step-num">2</div><h3>Choose Tenure & Amount</h3><p>Select the deposit tenure based on your liquidity needs. Opt for cumulative FD for long-term wealth building or non-cumulative for regular income. Decide the deposit amount (min ₹5,000 for most banks).</p></div>
              <div class="step-card"><div class="step-num">3</div><h3>Complete KYC & Apply</h3><p>Open FD online through net banking or visit a branch. KYC documents include PAN card, Aadhaar, and a passport photo. Most banks allow instant FD creation through their mobile apps.</p></div>
              <div class="step-card"><div class="step-num">4</div><h3>Earn Guaranteed Interest</h3><p>Your FD begins earning interest from the deposit date. Track maturity dates and set up auto-renewal if desired. Interest can be credited monthly, quarterly, or at maturity based on your choice.</p></div>
            </div>
          </div>

